"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-penny-heyns-tatjana-smith-already-sa-greatest-olympian\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 63, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15, \"end\": 18, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9996520060747143, \"rank\": 0.00034776579785025764, \"text\": \"Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbPenny Heyns: Tatjana is already 'SA's greatest Olympian'  Penny Heyns says Tatjana Smith has already surpassed her, and all others, when it comes to Team SA success at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 65, \"to\": 385, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 107, \"end\": 110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9996520060747143, \"rank\": 0.00034776579785025764, \"text\": \"Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 204, \"end\": 215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penelope_Heyns\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Penny Heyns\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penelope_Heyns\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penelope_Heyns\"}, {\"begin\": 237, \"end\": 239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.505683187795521e-16, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 251, \"end\": 259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999991984453602, \"rank\": 8.015552152563289e-07, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 262, \"end\": 273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penelope_Heyns\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Penny Heyns\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penelope_Heyns\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penelope_Heyns\"}, {\"begin\": 358, \"end\": 360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.505683187795521e-16, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Penny Heyns is the only other athlete in the history of the Olympics to do the 100m and 200m breaststroke double when she obliterated the field at the 1996 Atlanta Games, but the baton has well and truly be handed over to Tatjana Smith.\", \"from\": 387, \"to\": 623, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 387, \"end\": 398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penelope_Heyns\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Penny Heyns\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penelope_Heyns\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penelope_Heyns\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Heyns has backed golden girl Tatjana to do the 100m and 200m breaststroke double and become the second swimmer to achieve the feat at an Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 625, \"to\": 776, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As far as South Africa is concerned, Tatjana has surpassed me in the Olympic sense,\\\" Heyns toldShowmax.\", \"from\": 778, \"to\": 882, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 789, \"end\": 801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999999993669917, \"rank\": 6.330157629615607e-10, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I had two golds and a bronze, and she has two golds and a silver, and will most likely get another medal tonight.\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 997, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's just a matter of what colour she gets.\\\"\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1042, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On Monday night, Smith had to come from behind to win the 100m breaststroke final after China's Tang Qianting threw down the gauntlet with a blistering first 50m in the pool.\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1218, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1132, \"end\": 1137, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999989223530414, \"rank\": 5.748427473102558e-07, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1140, \"end\": 1153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tang_Qianting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tang Qianting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tang_Qianting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tang_Qianting\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Heyns says while she was confident that Smith would get a podium finish, even she was left surprised by the SA swimmer's push at the end of the 100m race to grab gold.\", \"from\": 1219, \"to\": 1386, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1327, \"end\": 1329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.505683187795521e-16, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was confident that Tatjana was going to get on the podium for the 100m breaststroke, but I did not know where she would finish as she was ranked fifth and there were two swimmers in that race that have gone faster than her, but I knew Tatjana is a fighter.\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1647, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When I saw her in the heats and in the semi-finals, I thought that she would easily be in front of them for the whole way in the race, so Monday night was a little bit of a nail biter.\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1834, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But, in terms of being confident of her grabbing gold, that confidence was more in the 200m breaststroke.\\\"\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 1942, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith will swim at the 200m breaststroke finals tonight (Thursday) together with her compatriot Kaylene Corbett, and the race will be shown live onShowmax, with the schedule suggestingit will get under way just after 21:00.\", \"from\": 1944, \"to\": 2167, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2040, \"end\": 2055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylene_Corbett\", \"score\": 0.9999999961760295, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaylene Corbett\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylene_Corbett\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylene_Corbett\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She (Smith) is the highest decorated Olympian of all sports in South Africa,\\\" Heyns commented.\", \"from\": 2169, \"to\": 2264, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2207, \"end\": 2215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999991984453602, \"rank\": 8.015552152563289e-07, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 2233, \"end\": 2245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999999993669917, \"rank\": 6.330157629615607e-10, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As far as where does she rank in terms of the greatest swimmers in the country, depends on how you look at it.\", \"from\": 2265, \"to\": 2376, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some might say that Chad le Clos is the most decorated and successful swimmer because he has a lot of World Cup medals and World Short Course medals.\", \"from\": 2377, \"to\": 2526, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2397, \"end\": 2409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad_le_Clos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chad le Clos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad_le_Clos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad_le_Clos\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But quite honestly, most American, and Australian swimmers do not swim World Cups and World Shorts, and Tatjana does not compete in Short Course.\", \"from\": 2528, \"to\": 2674, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2568, \"end\": 2578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.8085532369246131, \"rank\": 0.23444085827873268, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only thing that really matters for a lot of swimmers is the Olympic events.\", \"from\": 2675, \"to\": 2754, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"While Chad has one gold and three silvers, I think Tatjana trumps him.\", \"from\": 2756, \"to\": 2827, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2763, \"end\": 2767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad\", \"score\": 0.9999999416813824, \"rank\": 2.3242159967873475e-08, \"text\": \"Chad\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I would like to see her break more world records.\", \"from\": 2828, \"to\": 2877, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Chad has two Short Course world records, and Tatjana has one Long Course world record that was only recently broken by a Russian swimmer.\\\"\", \"from\": 2878, \"to\": 3016, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2878, \"end\": 2882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad\", \"score\": 0.9999999416813824, \"rank\": 2.3242159967873475e-08, \"text\": \"Chad\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad\"}, {\"begin\": 2999, \"end\": 3006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"score\": 0.6142337719112018, \"rank\": 0.6269311112592697, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Heyns has also been impressed by South Africa's other swimmers in Paris and is excited to see Le Clos compete at the games.\", \"from\": 3018, \"to\": 3141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3051, \"end\": 3063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999999993669917, \"rank\": 6.330157629615607e-10, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 3084, \"end\": 3089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998376552, \"rank\": 1.6238689320962985e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Of course I am excited to see Chad swim, and to see how well he would do.\", \"from\": 3143, \"to\": 3217, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3174, \"end\": 3178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad\", \"score\": 0.9999999416813824, \"rank\": 2.3242159967873475e-08, \"text\": \"Chad\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's difficult to tell, as he will be swimming against a couple of really fast 100m butterfly swimmers, who have swum faster than he has ever swum, so Chad's going to have to swim a personal best time if he wants to go through to the final and stand a chance of a podium finish.\\\"\", \"from\": 3218, \"to\": 3497, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3369, \"end\": 3373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad\", \"score\": 0.9999999416813824, \"rank\": 2.3242159967873475e-08, \"text\": \"Chad\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring!\", \"from\": 3499, \"to\": 3578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3499, \"end\": 3502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WIN_Television\", \"score\": 0.9999695039021298, \"rank\": 3.049434365638972e-05, \"text\": \"WIN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WIN_Television\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WIN_Television\"}, {\"begin\": 3503, \"end\": 3505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DVD_region_code\", \"score\": 0.946371758158642, \"rank\": 0.055807843676952094, \"text\": \"R2\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DVD_region_code\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DVD_region_code\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news 